Applying Boolean Logic,\begin{align}P(A)=1 \implies A=1\label{eq1}\\ P(A|B)=\frac{P(AB)}{P(B)} \end{align} Using \eqref{eq1}, \begin{align} P(A|B)&=\frac{P(1\times B)}{P(B)}\\ &=\frac{P(B)}{P(B)}=1\\ P(B|A)&=\frac{P(AB)}{P(A)}\\ &=\frac{P(B)}{P(A)}=\dfrac{\frac{1}{2}}{1}=\frac{1}{2}\end{align}Hence the correct answer is option 4).